text.__SUMMARY__:
Grevillea insignis, commonly known as wax grevillea,  is a shrub species which is endemic to  the south-west of Western Australia.  The species was first formally described in 1855 in Hooker's Journal of Botany and Kew Garden Miscellany.Two subspecies are currently recognised:

Grevillea insignis subsp. elliotii Olde & Marriott.
Grevillea insignis Kippist ex Meisn. subsp. insignis
